PILOT PEN TENNIS PRESENTED BY SCHICK
August 23, 2007
Agustin Calleri
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT









   THE MODERATOR:  Questions, please. 

 Q.  You were up 5-4 and 40-Love.  Must have felt very confident at that point.  What happened? 
 AGUSTIN CALLERI:  I think that James played well when I had match point.  When I came to the net James was playing well, and that's it. 

 Q.  How difficult was it?  James obviously has so many supporters chanting his name all the time.  Can you block that out, or is that difficult, especially when it gets to crunch time? 
 AGUSTIN CALLERI:  No.  That's normal.  The people want James to win and it doesn't both me. 

 Q.  The way you were serving going into the tiebreak, did you think you were still in pretty good shape to win the tiebreak? 
 AGUSTIN CALLERI:  I didn't serve well in the tiebreak and James got a lot of confidence during that tiebreak. 
 He played well as well.  In the third set James played with a lot of confidence. 

 Q.  When you have three match points like that, how tough is a loss like this to take when you have the match on your racquet like you did tonight? 
 AGUSTIN CALLERI:  Of course it bothers me.  I played very well until that point and then I lose the match.  That's sports.  That's the way it goes. 

 Q.  It appeared at the end that you and James exchanged a few words when you left the court.  Can you make a comment on what happened? 
 AGUSTIN CALLERI:  That's between the two of us.  I don't want to comment on it. 

 Q.  What did it start with?  What did the comments originate from? 
 THE MODERATOR:  He just said he didn't want to comment on it.  Anything else?  Thank you. 



END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT